{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312030957fac12be92c874367","session_id":"0f417c3a-586b-4d95-85f1-7addd373f935","message":{"id":"20260312030957fac12be92c874367","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile my code review findings and generate the review report.\n\n---\n\n## F-002 Phase 6 Review Report\n\n### Code Review Summary\n\n**Verdict: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n---\n\n### 1. Spec Compliance Analysis\n\n| User Story | Status | Notes |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| US-1: Pipeline Command | ✅ PASS | All subcommands (run/status/logs/stop) implemented |\n| US-2: Bugfix Command | ✅ PASS | Delegates correctly with type=bugfix |\n| US-3: Status Query | ✅ PASS | Returns pipeline list with status |\n| US-4: Logs Query | ✅ PASS | 4000 char threshold implemented (D3) |\n| US-5: Stop Pipeline | ✅ PASS | Returns confirmation message |\n| US-6: Error Guidance | ✅ PASS | Clear error messages with suggestions |\n| US-7: Authorization Guard | ✅ PASS | All commands require auth (D2) |\n\n| NFR | Status | Notes |\n|-----|--------|-------|\n| NFR-1: Extensibility | ✅ PASS | Registry supports dynamic command registration |\n| NFR-2: Testability | ✅ PASS | Handlers can be mocked via DI |\n| NFR-3: Performance | ✅ PASS | Parser < 50ms verified in tests |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Test Results\n\n| Test File | Tests | Status |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| parser.test.js | 18 | ✅ PASS |\n| registry.test.js | 14 | ✅ PASS |\n| validator.test.js | 14 | ✅ PASS |\n| formatter.test.js | 10 | ✅ PASS |\n| handlers.test.js | 12 | ✅ PASS |\n| f002-command-router.integration.test.js | 6 | ✅ PASS |\n| **Total** | **74** | **ALL PASS** |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Code Review Findings\n\n#### HIGH Severity\n\nNone found.\n\n#### MEDIUM Severity\n\n| ID | File | Line | Issue | Suggestion |\n|----|------|------|-------|------------|\n| M1 | `src/bot/commands/validator.js` | 102-115 | `getParamValue()` has incomplete positional arg mapping. The function checks `positionalIndex = 0` but doesn't properly map params by name. | Consider using a proper param-to-position mapping or document this limitation. |\n\n#### LOW Severity\n\n| ID | File | Line | Issue | Suggestion |\n|----|------|------|-------|------------|\n| L1 | `src/bot/commands/index.js` | 119-123 | `registerDefaultCommands()` is empty but exported. | Either implement or remove to avoid confusion. |\n| L2 | `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` | 67 | Default action falls through to status silently if no subcommand. | Consider explicit handling or documentation. |\n| L3 | `tests/integration/f002-user-stories.integration.test.js` | - | Test file has recursion warning when run with node --test. | Refactor to avoid nested test() calls. |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Security Review\n\n| Check | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| Authorization on all commands | ✅ | All handlers set `requiresAuth: true` |\n| No sensitive info in errors | ✅ | UNAUTHORIZED message is generic |\n| No hardcoded credentials | ✅ | None found |\n| Input validation | ✅ | Validator checks types and enums |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Decisions Compliance\n\n| Decision | Status | Implementation |\n|----------|--------|----------------|\n| D1: `/planner` as independent type | ✅ | `plannerMeta` with type=planner default |\n| D2: Reuse `isAllowedUser()` | ✅ | `index.js:95` calls `isAllowedUser(userId)` |\n| D3: Logs threshold 4000 chars | ✅ | `logs.js:30` defines `FILE_THRESHOLD = 4000` |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Alias Mapping Verification\n\n| Alias | Maps To | Test Coverage |\n|-------|---------|---------------|\n| `/p` | `/pipeline` | ✅ Verified |\n| `/b` | `/bugfix` | ✅ Verified |\n| `/s` | `/status` | ✅ Verified |\n| `/l` | `/logs` | ✅ Verified |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Integration with telegram.js\n\nThe integration is properly implemented:\n- Commands are registered via `registerPipelineCommands()` (line 420-427)\n- Router is called in `bot.on('text')` handler (line 500-504)\n- Help command uses `generateHelp()` (line 447)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Recommended Actions\n\n1. **Fix positional arg mapping** in validator.js (M1) - This could cause issues with commands that rely on positional arguments.\n\n2. **Fix test file recursion** in `f002-user-stories.integration.test.js` - The file has issues when run with node --test flag.\n\n3. **Document or implement** `registerDefaultCommands()` (L1) - Currently a no-op.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Verdict\n\n**PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n- No CRITICAL or security issues found\n- All 7 user stories implemented correctly\n- All NFRs met\n- 74 tests pass\n- 1 MEDIUM issue found (incomplete positional arg mapping)\n- 3 LOW issues found (code quality improvements)\n\nThe implementation correctly follows the spec and plan. The MEDIUM issue (M1) does not affect current functionality since commands use options (`--type=bugfix`) rather than positional args, but should be addressed for future extensibility.\n\n---\n\n**COMPLETION_SIGNAL**\n- Feature: F-002 Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n- Verdict: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n- Tests: 74/74 passing\n- Critical Issues: 0\n- High Issues: 0\n- Medium Issues: 1\n- Low Issues: 3"}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":98176,"output_tokens":1970,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4bfd019ea78fd92536fc7b2011","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:10:40.435Z","_requestId":"4b990aef1ee94c0d9951653ca0a8a1f1"}
